<Layout title="Math Resources" description="Recommended textbooks and resources for high school and university math students.">
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Math Resources</h1>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="page-content">
      <p>Here is a list of resources for studying and doing math.</p><h3 id="math-tools"><strong>Math Tools</strong></h3><ul><li><a href="https://www.desmos.com/calculator">Desmos</a> 2D Grapher, graphing functions and relations in the plane, also has a smartphone app</li><li><a href="https://www.geogebra.org/3d?lang=en">Geogebra 3D Grapher</a> for graphing surfaces in multivariable calculus</li></ul><h3 id="math-calculatorsfor-making-computations">Math Calculators - for Making Computations</h3><ul><li><a href="https://www.mathway.com/">Mathway</a> user-friendly calculator for many kinds of problems</li><li><a href="https://www.symbolab.com/solver">Symbolab</a> calculator for many kinds of problems</li><li><a href="https://photomath.app/en/">Photomath</a> smartphone app to solve math equations by picture, particularly basic and intermediate algebra</li><li><a href="https://www.wolframalpha.com/">WolframAlpha</a> high-powered computation for a wide variety of problems</li><li><a href="https://www.derivative-calculator.net/">Derivative calculator</a>, and <a href="https://www.integral-calculator.com/">Integral calculator</a></li></ul><h3 id="math-textbook-solutions">Math Textbook Solutions</h3><ul><li><a href="https://www.gradesaver.com/textbooks">GradeSaver</a> free textbook solutions</li><li><a href="https://www.bartleby.com/">Bartlby</a> free math textbook solutions</li><li><a href="https://quizlet.com/explanations">Quizlet</a> paid textbook solutions</li><li><a href="https://www.chegg.com/homework-help/solutions-manual">Chegg</a> paid textbook solutions</li></ul><h3 id="resources-for-studying-math-video-etc"><strong>Resources for Studying Math (Video etc.)</strong></h3><ul><li><a href="https://khanacademy.org/">Khan Academy</a> focus on basics and practice exercises</li><li>PatrickJMT (<a href="http://patrickjmt.com/">Website</a>, <a href="https://www.youtube.com/user/patrickJMT">Youtube</a>) videos with focus on by-hand computation and steps</li><li><a href="https://tutorial.math.lamar.edu/">Paul's Online Math Notes</a> intuitive and detailed examples and computations, for algebra, calculus, and differential equations</li><li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/c/3blue1brown/featured">3Blue1Brown (3B1B)</a> videos with inspiring and beautiful animations</li><li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/c/ProfessorLeonard/playlists">Professor Leonard</a> videos with clear and intuitive explanations</li><li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/c/Freemathvideos">Brian McLogan</a> videos with basic explanations and enthusiasm</li><li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/user/Mathbyfives">Mathbyfives</a> videos with eccentric, enthusiastic, and funny explanations</li><li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCEWpbFLzoYGPfuWUMFPSaoA">Organic Chemistry Tutor</a> videos with focus on by-hand computation and steps, with lots of examples</li><li><a href="https://brilliant.org/">Brilliant</a> paid website for intuitive and exploratory learning</li></ul><h3 id="scanning-apps-for-scanning-written-work">Scanning Apps, for Scanning Written Work</h3><ul><li>Adobe scan</li><li>CamScanner</li><li>iOS Notes app (built-in)</li></ul><h3 id="advanced-math">Advanced Math</h3><ul><li><a href="http://tug.ctan.org/info/lshort/english/lshort.pdf">The Not So Short Introduction to LaTeX</a>, guide for learning LaTeX</li><li><a href="https://oeis.org/wiki/List_of_LaTeX_mathematical_symbols">List of LaTeX math symbols</a></li><li><a href="https://detexify.kirelabs.org/classify.html">Detexify</a> for figuring out the code for an unknown LaTeX symbol, by sketching it</li><li><a href="https://approach0.xyz/search/">Approach Zero</a> search engine which recognizes LaTeX math symbols</li></ul><h3 id="free-scientific-papers">Free Scientific Papers</h3><ul><li><a href="https://sci-hub.mksa.top/">Scihub</a>, for scientific papers (I've heard a lot about this, but haven't used it personally)</li></ul>
    </div>
